com.jcabi.immutable

Class ArraySortedSet<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.jcabi.immutable.ArraySortedSet<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Value key type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<T>, Collection<T>, Set<T>, SortedSet<T>

    @Immutable
@Loggable(value=1)
public final class ArraySortedSet<T>
extends Object
implements SortedSet<T>
    Sorted Set on top of array.

    This class is truly immutable. This means that it never changes its encapsulated values and is annotated with &#64;Immutable annotation.

    Since:
    0.1
    Version:
    $Id$
    Author:
    Yegor Bugayenko (yegor@tpc2.com)
